{
  "stem": "27443.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And a lot of people-- a lot of young girls, like me, not seeing a way, that we'll never survive between the chimneys, and between the hardship, and between the beating that we had daily, a lot of girls committed suicide by throwing themselves on the electric wire.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "There was an outhouse by the wires that we used it as toilets.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And a lot of girls, instead to go to the outhouse, they never came back, because they committed suicide.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We never thought that we were going to be liberated from that camp.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, many times.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We never thought that we were going to ever be liberated.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] As a young girl, I had a grandmother living in Zgierz.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was not far from Lodz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When I used to go to her for vacation-- and I was a very young child-- she taught me to say Modeh Ani every morning.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And it's maybe now that I am an aged woman-- I somehow believed, being under these circumstances, that every morning I recited Modeh Ani.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I said [INAUDIBLE] before I went to bed-- to bed, if you could call it a bed.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But somehow the belief in God that I was brought up with, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and being young probably, and the hope that I will still see my parents someday or my brothers, maybe the hope kept me alive.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Even to this day, I never miss Modeh Ani in my life.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I recite this every morning.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] In Majdanek, we worked in fields.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We were marched every morning into fields.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And there was always a whip above your head.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You were not allowed to pick up your head from the work that did.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
